        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "On March 27, as the coronavirus was spreading, Trump’s SEC sided with Amazon and issued a so-called “no action” ruling saying the agency concurred with the company and would not recommend any adverse enforcement action against executives if they blocked shareholders from voting on the proposal.",
